    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Trails in SA"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"9bfac51b-cc05-5a99-8941-ecb82f4c4e99","excerpt":"This is a fun hiking, running and cycling spot near Johannesburg. There are a number of trails to choose from and a small waterfall to check out on the routes…","html":"<p>This is a fun hiking, running and cycling spot near Johannesburg. There are a number of trails to choose from and a small waterfall to check out on the routes.</p>\n<p>The trails are as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>6km Green Easy</li>\n<li>10km Blue Moderate</li>\n<li>19km Black Difficult</li>\n<li>25km Red Technical</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 400px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/trails-data/static/d0531ed475f583552ff0c9fe61f45aff/4b190/kings-kloof.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"kings kloof waterfall\"\n        title=\"kings kloof waterfall\"\n        src=\"/trails-data/static/d0531ed475f583552ff0c9fe61f45aff/066f9/kings-kloof.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/trails-data/static/d0531ed475f583552ff0c9fe61f45aff/b9e9c/kings-kloof.jpg 100w,\n/trails-data/static/d0531ed475f583552ff0c9fe61f45aff/e07e9/kings-kloof.jpg 200w,\n/trails-data/static/d0531ed475f583552ff0c9fe61f45aff/066f9/kings-kloof.jpg 400w,\n/trails-data/static/d0531ed475f583552ff0c9fe61f45aff/b4294/kings-kloof.jpg 600w,\n/trails-data/static/d0531ed475f583552ff0c9fe61f45aff/4b190/kings-kloof.jpg 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>There is a large parking lot and a small coffee shop that sells a bunch of things to eat and drink.</p>\n<p>The routes are a little windy because I think it’s made for cycling so you’ll be looping back on yourself in a few spots. It’s fairly well marked, but may be confusing sometimes.</p>\n<p>The waterfall is a few 100 meters off the main routes but worth checking out. You cross the river feeding the waterfall throughout the route. There is also a nice lake, which seems popular for people to camp and fish at. We also saw a bunch of cows.</p>\n<p>We did the blue hiking trail which was a nice hike past the waterfall.</p>\n<p>The cost is R40pp which is good.</p>\n<p>It’s only open on public holidays and weekends 5:30am and closes at 15:00pm. No dogs allowed.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/gauteng/kings-kloof/","province":"gauteng"},"frontmatter":{"trailName":"Kings Kloof","date":"14 December 2020","location":"https://goo.gl/maps/AqeQxaW2EPKmmcK78","routes":"https://www.alltrails.com/trail/south-africa/gauteng/kings-kloof-farm-blue-route","link":"https://www.kingskloofvenue.co.za/","activity":["running","walking","cycling","hiking"],"free":false}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/mpumalanga/kaapsehoop-nature-trail/"},"frontmatter":{"title":""}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/gauteng/kloofendal-nature-reserve/"},"frontmatter":{"title":""}}},"pageContext":{"id":"9bfac51b-cc05-5a99-8941-ecb82f4c4e99","previousPostId":"1fffa6e2-8010-5374-9613-8fe4561418c3","nextPostId":"53933f9f-bd47-51a0-8c64-e0d6eaac35d5"}},
